pageContext.claim: “If we send a car into China, they charge 25 percent. When China sends a car to us, we charge 2.5 percent.”
pageContext.analysis: When Trump said this, China had announced it was cutting the 25 percent tariff to 15 percent as of July 1. Trump is wrong to suggest no American cars are sold in China. General Motors sells more cars in China (3.9 million) than in the US (3 million) and saw its China business grow 13 percent in 2016.
